    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-08T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="67"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/613</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-08T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7180. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>307. Your No. 365. Embassy No. 9311, April 2, 9 p.m. We approve of the statement
                    of the functions of local trade committee in northern European capitals as set
                    out in Foreign Office communication which you quote. Our ministers at these
                    capitals are being notified of this approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
